1
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:36,680
Dongzi...

2
00:01:37,239 --> 00:01:38,120
They found him a donor.

3
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:40,319
The hospital called me last night.

4
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:42,480
They said he's first on the list now.

5
00:01:43,159 --> 00:01:44,439
But then they said

6
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,519
the donor's family hadn't decided yet,

7
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:47,760
so we still have to wait.

8
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:49,680
What a mess.

9
00:01:49,879 --> 00:01:51,560
My heart's been in my throat ever since.

10
00:01:51,599 --> 00:01:53,159
I'm just hanging there,

11
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,200
unable to move either way.

12
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,799
Please, God.

13
00:01:56,959 --> 00:01:59,200
Don't torture us anymore.

14
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:10,360
All right.

15
00:02:10,719 --> 00:02:11,319
Thank you, Dr. Fang.

16
00:02:11,479 --> 00:02:11,919
You're welcome.

17
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:22,719
Anything else?

18
00:02:26,319 --> 00:02:27,840
Lu Dadong's pulmonary embolism

19
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:28,919
is only the result.

20
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:30,800
The root cause is either hypercoagulability

21
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:32,879
or an existing thrombus.

22
00:02:33,159 --> 00:02:34,879
Catheter thrombectomy treats the symptom, not the cause.

23
00:02:36,319 --> 00:02:37,240
That's possible.

24
00:02:37,919 --> 00:02:38,719
Even with thrombectomy now,

25
00:02:38,719 --> 00:02:39,759
we can't be sure

26
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:40,800
the clot can be fully removed.

27
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,879
If his hypercoagulable state isn't corrected,

28
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,159
after the heart transplant,

29
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,840
he'll need immunosuppressants,

30
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:47,360
which will worsen the hypercoagulability.

31
00:02:47,719 --> 00:02:48,840
Then he's very likely

32
00:02:48,919 --> 00:02:50,039
to develop another pulmonary embolism.

33
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,680
But all his current indicators

34
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,439
are still acceptable.

35
00:03:00,479 --> 00:03:02,120
It's not as serious as you think.

36
00:03:04,639 --> 00:03:05,199
Are you really

37
00:03:05,199 --> 00:03:06,360
not going to reconsider?

38
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,800
I know Xiaorui is also waiting.

39
00:03:23,479 --> 00:03:24,680
What were you trying to do just now?

40
00:03:25,159 --> 00:03:26,240
This is none of your business.

41
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,319
I spoke out of turn.

42
00:03:28,879 --> 00:03:29,639
I'm sorry.

43
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,039
I tend to be blunt,

44
00:03:33,759 --> 00:03:36,240
but I'm telling the truth.

45
00:03:37,039 --> 00:03:38,199
You know it too.

46
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:39,800
Lu Dadong has already

47
00:03:39,879 --> 00:03:41,280
had so many complications.

48
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:42,840
If you force this

49
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,840
transplant through,

50
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:44,759
the risk of

51
00:03:44,759 --> 00:03:45,800
a poor postoperative outcome

52
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,039
is much higher than Xiaorui's.

53
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,919
So this precious donor heart

54
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:52,520
would be of greater value to Xiaorui.

55
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:53,879
The recipient ranking

56
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:54,719
and organ allocation

57
00:03:54,759 --> 00:03:55,919
are determined by the system.

58
00:03:56,879 --> 00:03:58,120
There are strict standards

59
00:03:58,159 --> 00:03:58,759
and oversight.

60
00:03:59,919 --> 00:04:01,199
You used to be a doctor.

61
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:01,840
You know

62
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:03,919
doctors have no right to decide

63
00:04:03,919 --> 00:04:05,120
whose life is worth more.

64
00:04:05,479 --> 00:04:06,360
Then try looking at it

65
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,520
from another angle.

66
00:04:09,719 --> 00:04:10,919
Think from Director Lin

67
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:12,639
and Dr. Fang's perspective.

68
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:14,639
Think as a sister

69
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,160
and future brother-in-law.

70
00:04:16,199 --> 00:04:17,319
Think about it that way.

71
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:18,959
He's family.

72
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,120
He's one of your own.

73
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:22,439
Would you still be

74
00:04:22,439 --> 00:04:23,319
so resolute?

75
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,920
But doesn't everyone have family?

76
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,199
Liang Mei's parents have passed away.

77
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,279
She and Dadong are newlyweds.

78
00:04:36,319 --> 00:04:37,240
They only have each other.

79
00:04:38,279 --> 00:04:39,360
If she loses Dadong now,

80
00:04:40,199 --> 00:04:41,040
what will she do?

81
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:44,040
They're all suffering.

82
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:46,560
I feel for Liang Mei too.

83
00:04:48,199 --> 00:04:49,040
But if this happened

84
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,480
to me,

85
00:04:51,079 --> 00:04:52,079
to my family,

86
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:53,839
even to my son,

87
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,519
I'd fight with everything I had

88
00:04:55,519 --> 00:04:57,240
to get that heart.

89
00:05:02,279 --> 00:05:03,920
If that heart went to Xiaorui,

90
00:05:04,959 --> 00:05:06,079
his life would change

91
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,480
completely.

92
00:05:07,759 --> 00:05:09,160
His future would be full of hope.

93
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,120
But what if

94
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,079
it goes to Lu Dadong?

95
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,959
If Lin Yi performs the surgery himself,

96
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:19,759
and Xiaorui

97
00:05:19,759 --> 00:05:20,959
misses this chance

98
00:05:20,959 --> 00:05:22,000
and something happens to him,

99
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:22,839
or worse...

100
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:26,639
what would Lin Yi do?

101
00:05:27,959 --> 00:05:29,480
Would he ever recover from it?

102
00:05:30,839 --> 00:05:32,480
And what about Dr. Fang?

103
00:05:37,279 --> 00:05:38,120
Acute pulmonary embolism

104
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,560
is a contraindication to transplantation.

105
00:05:40,079 --> 00:05:41,279
Anticoagulation must come first,

106
00:05:41,759 --> 00:05:43,360
followed by thrombolysis or

107
00:05:43,399 --> 00:05:44,439
pulmonary artery thrombectomy.

108
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,319
If the embolism is fully resolved

109
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:47,319
and causes no

110
00:05:47,319 --> 00:05:48,800
permanent right heart failure,

111
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,360
transplant eligibility may be restored.

112
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:54,519
What if a

113
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,759
twenty-year-old patient

114
00:05:56,519 --> 00:05:57,839
receives a heart transplant?

115
00:05:58,800 --> 00:05:59,720
Would the prognosis be good?

116
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:01,680
That's hard to say.

117
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,199
But clinical data show

118
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,199
that for patients in their twenties,

119
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:05,720
after heart transplantation,

120
00:06:05,959 --> 00:06:07,120
the one-year survival rate

121
00:06:07,199 --> 00:06:08,800
is generally above 90 percent.

122
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,279
Among those who survive,

123
00:06:10,839 --> 00:06:12,800
over 90 percent recover to

124
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,000
NYHA Class I,

125
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,959
meaning their function is like a healthy person's.

126
00:06:16,319 --> 00:06:18,199
They can finish school,

127
00:06:18,319 --> 00:06:19,360
work, and travel normally.

128
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,040
What if I'm

129
00:06:22,079 --> 00:06:22,759
not first

130
00:06:22,759 --> 00:06:23,959
on the recipient list?

131
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:27,839
What are my chances of getting a donor?

132
00:07:15,199 --> 00:07:15,839
Director Zhou,

133
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,959
this isn't a line for coffee.

134
00:07:19,759 --> 00:07:21,319
It isn't giving up a subway seat.

135
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,439
This is life and death.

136
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,519
I know people will condemn me.

137
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,800
You'll think I'm cold-blooded too.

138
00:07:27,199 --> 00:07:28,639
But now that things have come

139
00:07:28,639 --> 00:07:29,560
this far,

140
00:07:30,079 --> 00:07:31,480
I still have to say something selfish.

141
00:07:33,879 --> 00:07:34,839
This chance is rare.

142
00:07:35,639 --> 00:07:36,600
Family comes first.

143
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:54,399
What am I supposed to choose?

144
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:00,160
Tell me.

145
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:03,279
What should I choose?

146
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:32,639
Dr. Fang,

147
00:08:34,759 --> 00:08:35,639
am I no longer eligible

148
00:08:35,639 --> 00:08:36,360
for a transplant?

149
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:37,759
Is it impossible now?

150
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,000
Don't overthink it.

151
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:41,080
Let me listen to your chest first.

152
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:44,759
I'm begging you.

153
00:08:45,279 --> 00:08:45,799
Save me.

154
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,480
You have to save me.

155
00:08:47,799 --> 00:08:48,519
I want to live.

156
00:08:49,039 --> 00:08:50,679
Xiaomei is waiting outside for me.

157
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,360
Don't be afraid.

158
00:08:52,679 --> 00:08:53,639
I'm trying to save you.

159
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:54,840
We all are.

160
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,759
Come on. Let me listen.

161
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:06,879
Take a breath.

162
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,720
How is he now?

163
00:09:16,759 --> 00:09:17,639
Does he still have a chance?

164
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,600
We can't be sure yet.

165
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,519
If I get the heart this time

166
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,480
and the transplant goes smoothly,

167
00:09:32,879 --> 00:09:33,840
I'll care for

168
00:09:33,919 --> 00:09:35,120
the donor's family for the rest of my life

169
00:09:38,559 --> 00:09:39,679
to repay them for saving me.

170
00:09:49,559 --> 00:09:50,360
You're thinking too far ahead.

171
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:52,759
Donor and recipient

172
00:09:52,879 --> 00:09:54,120
are kept mutually anonymous.

173
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,320
We can't know

174
00:09:55,399 --> 00:09:56,200
who the donor was.

175
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,240
You don't know either?

176
00:10:00,759 --> 00:10:01,360
Besides,

177
00:10:02,039 --> 00:10:03,279
the donor's family

178
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:05,159
hasn't made the final decision.

179
00:10:06,799 --> 00:10:08,440
If it doesn't work out this time,

180
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,200
we'll wait for the next one.

181
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:14,320
The next one?

182
00:10:16,799 --> 00:10:18,039
When will that be?

183
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,000
I'm afraid I won't live that long.

184
00:10:34,159 --> 00:10:35,039
You'll save me,

185
00:10:38,519 --> 00:10:38,960
right?

186
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:54,759
Lu Dadong is hypoxic.

187
00:11:02,159 --> 00:11:02,600
Yi.

188
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:06,120
A patient has had

189
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:06,799
an emergency.

190
00:11:07,799 --> 00:11:08,559
I need to go check.

191
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:12,240
Yi.

192
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:19,960
I'll wait right here for you.

193
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:43,200
The family has agreed to donate the organs.

194
00:11:48,759 --> 00:11:49,799
You don't have to do anything.

195
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:52,039
Just don't push too hard.

196
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:54,639
Let events take their course.

197
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:57,440
Then...

198
00:11:59,639 --> 00:12:00,879
keeping your family alive

199
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:02,879
is also your responsibility.

200
00:12:04,879 --> 00:12:06,120
The required paperwork...

201
00:12:07,639 --> 00:12:08,480
and supporting documents—

202
00:12:08,759 --> 00:12:09,519
don't worry about them.

203
00:12:09,759 --> 00:12:10,519
I'll handle everything.

204
00:12:11,519 --> 00:12:13,159
You only need to perform the surgery.

205
00:12:14,799 --> 00:12:15,879
If you can't bring yourself to do it,

206
00:12:16,879 --> 00:12:17,919
I can operate

207
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,360
on Xiaorui instead.

208
00:12:21,919 --> 00:12:23,879
This donor is exceptionally good.

209
00:12:24,519 --> 00:12:26,000
It's a once-in-a-lifetime chance.

210
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:28,639
Lin Yi,

211
00:12:30,799 --> 00:12:31,759
don't let Xiaorui blame you.

212
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:34,519
And don't leave yourself with regret.

213
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,600
This is the choice you should make.

214
00:12:59,120 --> 00:12:59,840
Don't worry.

215
00:13:25,559 --> 00:13:26,080
Yi,

216
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:29,120
I'll wait right here for you.

217
00:13:51,399 --> 00:13:52,720
Xiaorui is

218
00:13:52,759 --> 00:13:53,799
my only family in this world.

219
00:13:55,559 --> 00:13:56,480
When my brother died,

220
00:13:56,519 --> 00:13:57,480
I promised him

221
00:14:00,039 --> 00:14:01,360
I'd take good care of Xiaorui.

222
00:14:09,159 --> 00:14:10,360
I know what you're thinking.

223
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:13,840
But calm down.

224
00:14:22,919 --> 00:14:23,840
If you were me,

225
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:32,879
what would you choose?

226
00:14:56,519 --> 00:14:57,039
Lin Yi,

227
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:39,000
don't blame me.

228
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:14,919
Director Lin.

229
00:16:15,159 --> 00:16:16,240
I only have one wish now:

230
00:16:16,399 --> 00:16:17,120
to keep getting treatment

231
00:16:18,159 --> 00:16:19,399
and recover as soon as I can.

232
00:16:20,159 --> 00:16:20,879
Then when I get out,

233
00:16:20,879 --> 00:16:21,759
I'll earn more money,

234
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:23,320
buy Xiaomei a proper ring,

235
00:16:23,919 --> 00:16:25,080
and give her the wedding she deserves.

236
00:16:25,559 --> 00:16:26,360
Then we'll have two kids,

237
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:27,679
a boy and a girl.

238
00:16:29,039 --> 00:16:29,559
That sounds good.

239
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:32,480
Yi,

240
00:16:34,759 --> 00:16:35,559
you'll save me,

241
00:16:39,159 --> 00:16:39,600
right?

242
00:16:41,399 --> 00:16:42,080
Don't worry.

243
00:16:43,519 --> 00:16:44,720
I'll take good care of Xiaorui.

244
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,799
Keeping your family alive

245
00:16:48,759 --> 00:16:49,799
is also your responsibility.

246
00:16:50,919 --> 00:16:52,720
This donor is exceptionally good.

247
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:55,000
It's a once-in-a-lifetime chance.

248
00:16:57,159 --> 00:16:57,600
Lin Yi,

249
00:16:59,799 --> 00:17:00,799
don't let Xiaorui blame you.

250
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:03,440
And don't leave yourself with regret.

251
00:17:19,039 --> 00:17:20,480
In the future, at this hospital,

252
00:17:20,759 --> 00:17:21,880
you'll meet countless patients.

253
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:24,640
They may seem like

254
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:26,240
strangers who have nothing to do with you.

255
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,359
But I want you to remember:

256
00:17:31,480 --> 00:17:32,440
every patient

257
00:17:34,119 --> 00:17:35,559
has a family behind them.

258
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,119
Every one of them

259
00:17:38,799 --> 00:17:39,839
has their own story.

260
00:17:41,519 --> 00:17:42,640
I hope you'll remember

261
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,599
each and every one of them—

262
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:46,519
their names,

263
00:17:48,319 --> 00:17:48,880
their faces,

264
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:51,279
and their smiles.

265
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:54,960
I don't know what others believe,

266
00:17:56,440 --> 00:17:57,799
but as a doctor, I firmly believe

267
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:00,759
there are many things we cannot control.

268
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:04,480
Still, every life we save matters.

269
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:06,599
When facing a patient,

270
00:18:06,599 --> 00:18:08,039
we must never be careless.

271
00:18:10,799 --> 00:18:11,480
When facing a case,

272
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:12,920
we must never compromise or surrender.

273
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:15,640
When facing surgery,

274
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:16,880
we must give it everything we have.

275
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:21,680
So when I

276
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:22,920
became a doctor, I swore

277
00:18:24,079 --> 00:18:25,319
that every patient entrusted to me

278
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:28,680
would get everything I had.

279
00:18:28,759 --> 00:18:30,039
I would do whatever it took to save them

280
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,079
and leave myself no regrets.

281
00:18:56,519 --> 00:18:57,680
Dadong, how are you?

282
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:58,400
Feeling any better?

283
00:18:59,079 --> 00:18:59,759
Much better.

284
00:19:00,279 --> 00:19:02,000
Xiaomei, listen to me.

285
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,400
In the wardrobe at home,

286
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,319
the second drawer on the left—

287
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:09,960
there's a yellow box.

288
00:19:12,599 --> 00:19:13,640
Go home and find it.

289
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:17,319
What is it?

290
00:19:21,519 --> 00:19:22,359
It's for you.

291
00:19:23,599 --> 00:19:25,039
You'll understand when you see it.

292
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:34,680
I don't want it.

293
00:19:37,359 --> 00:19:38,279
When you're better,

294
00:19:38,279 --> 00:19:39,359
you can get it yourself.

295
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:51,039
Director Lin,

296
00:20:04,839 --> 00:20:05,599
Guo from the organ procurement organization

297
00:20:05,599 --> 00:20:06,200
got back to us.

298
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:07,799
The family has signed

299
00:20:08,039 --> 00:20:08,799
the donation consent form.

300
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:14,359
Based on Lu Dadong's

301
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:15,400
cardiac catheterization results,

302
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:17,000
he does have

303
00:20:17,039 --> 00:20:18,160
moderate pulmonary hypertension.

304
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:19,160
But his pulmonary vascular resistance

305
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:20,359
is below five Wood units.

306
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:21,720
And his acute

307
00:20:21,759 --> 00:20:22,720
vasodilator test shows

308
00:20:23,119 --> 00:20:24,599
good pulmonary vascular reactivity.

309
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:25,799
It doesn't rule out transplantation.

310
00:20:27,119 --> 00:20:28,279
He was hypoxic yesterday evening,

311
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:29,160
but currently

312
00:20:29,279 --> 00:20:30,759
his oxygen saturation is back to normal.

313
00:20:31,359 --> 00:20:33,119
The pulmonary infiltrates have also improved.

314
00:20:35,079 --> 00:20:36,440
So you all believe

315
00:20:37,079 --> 00:20:39,039
Lu Dadong is eligible for transplant,

316
00:20:39,319 --> 00:20:39,720
correct?

317
00:20:44,839 --> 00:20:45,279
Xiao Lin.

318
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:49,200
Director Lin.

319
00:20:51,799 --> 00:20:52,400
Are you sure?

320
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:00,400
I'm sure.

321
00:21:13,359 --> 00:21:13,759
Come on.

322
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:16,039
We're running out of time.

323
00:21:24,119 --> 00:21:24,640
Dadong.

324
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:26,799
Dadong! Dadong!

325
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:27,799
Xiaomei.

326
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:31,240
Xiaomei.

327
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:36,039
I found it.

328
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:40,680
Put it on.

329
00:21:58,599 --> 00:21:59,319
Does it look good?

330
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:01,440
Beautiful.

331
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:04,880
You made it?

332
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:07,680
I did.

333
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:09,880
Xiaorui taught me.

334
00:22:11,599 --> 00:22:12,400
It's so beautiful.

335
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:18,559
Like a princess.

336
00:22:22,319 --> 00:22:23,160
A princess.

337
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:25,440
My princess.

338
00:22:32,119 --> 00:22:32,920
Princess.

339
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,000
May it protect you.

340
00:22:57,039 --> 00:22:57,559
Don't be afraid.

341
00:22:58,880 --> 00:22:59,440
Don't be afraid.

342
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:03,079
Don't be afraid.

343
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:44,279
In your current state,

344
00:23:45,799 --> 00:23:46,759
should we switch lead surgeons?

345
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:53,839
No.

346
00:23:56,799 --> 00:23:57,480
I can do it.

347
00:24:03,799 --> 00:24:04,880
Ever since Xiaorui was diagnosed,

348
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:07,079
I've traveled everywhere

349
00:24:07,079 --> 00:24:08,079
performing heart transplants,

350
00:24:09,359 --> 00:24:10,200
training the team,

351
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:11,960
and building our credentials.

352
00:24:14,319 --> 00:24:14,960
Even though

353
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:16,119
the person inside isn't him,

354
00:24:19,839 --> 00:24:20,720
I'm ready.

355
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:53,200
Everyone,

356
00:24:53,519 --> 00:24:54,039
this operation

357
00:24:54,079 --> 00:24:54,960
is Dongli Hospital's

358
00:24:54,960 --> 00:24:56,279
first heart transplant,

359
00:24:56,759 --> 00:24:57,680
and this team's

360
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:58,720
first independent transplant

361
00:24:58,720 --> 00:24:59,839
since receiving accreditation.

362
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:03,920
I've imagined

363
00:25:03,960 --> 00:25:04,799
this day countless times.

364
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:07,160
Before we begin,

365
00:25:08,079 --> 00:25:09,319
I'd like everyone to join me

366
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:11,680
in thanking the donor

367
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:13,359
and the donor's family

368
00:25:13,359 --> 00:25:14,039
for this heart.

369
00:25:15,119 --> 00:25:15,599
Thank you

370
00:25:15,599 --> 00:25:17,319
for choosing kindness toward this world

371
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:18,880
even in the grief

372
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:19,559
of losing someone you loved.

373
00:25:20,920 --> 00:25:22,359
We will not betray that kindness.

374
00:25:24,359 --> 00:25:25,279
The effort

375
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:26,400
and training of this past year

376
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:27,720
will not be wasted.

377
00:25:29,079 --> 00:25:29,799
Now I need everyone

378
00:25:29,839 --> 00:25:30,880
to lend me your strength.

379
00:25:32,079 --> 00:25:33,160
With these hands,

380
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:35,480
let's connect two lives

381
00:25:37,559 --> 00:25:38,519
and let one life continue.

382
00:25:52,279 --> 00:25:53,759
The donor heart will arrive in thirty minutes.

383
00:25:55,640 --> 00:25:56,599
Prepare cardiopulmonary bypass.

384
00:25:57,039 --> 00:25:57,480
Copy.

385
00:29:07,519 --> 00:29:09,119
His hands are incredibly fast.

386
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:10,880
I'd say in all of Dongjiang,

387
00:29:11,279 --> 00:29:12,359
there are no more than three surgeons

388
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:13,440
at the operating table

389
00:29:13,759 --> 00:29:14,440
who can work that fast.

390
00:29:16,240 --> 00:29:17,440
In a heart transplant,

391
00:29:17,519 --> 00:29:18,720
speed is critical.

392
00:29:18,799 --> 00:29:19,720
The faster the anastomoses,

393
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:21,480
the shorter the myocardial ischemic time.

394
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:23,480
The less myocardial damage,

395
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:25,240
the better

396
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:26,400
the patient's prognosis.

397
00:29:27,599 --> 00:29:28,440
A new pair

398
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:29,240
of compression stockings for everyone.

399
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:30,519
Put them on properly.

400
00:29:30,880 --> 00:29:31,839
They'll prevent varicose veins.

401
00:29:32,599 --> 00:29:33,720
During this period,

402
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:34,759
no one is allowed to fall behind.

403
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:36,000
Stay sharp.

404
00:29:36,240 --> 00:29:36,720
Yes.

405
00:29:38,279 --> 00:29:39,519
With heart transplantation,

406
00:29:39,599 --> 00:29:41,119
successful surgery is only the first step.

407
00:29:41,319 --> 00:29:42,640
Perioperative monitoring

408
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:44,920
and postoperative management are critical.

409
00:29:45,319 --> 00:29:46,279
One small oversight

410
00:29:46,720 --> 00:29:47,920
could undo everything.

411
00:29:48,759 --> 00:29:49,839
Especially during

412
00:29:49,839 --> 00:29:50,799
the first 24 hours after surgery,

413
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:52,880
not a single step can go wrong.

414
00:29:53,319 --> 00:29:54,640
Keep a close eye on everything.

415
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:56,599
So for the next little while,

416
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:57,839
I'll need everyone to work extra hard.

417
00:29:59,000 --> 00:29:59,880
For the next few days,

418
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,000
Head Nurse Shen and I

419
00:30:01,039 --> 00:30:02,079
will stay in the

420
00:30:02,079 --> 00:30:02,799
comprehensive ICU around the clock.

421
00:30:03,119 --> 00:30:04,680
Report any problem immediately.

422
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:06,960
And thank you, Head Nurse Shen, for holding the fort.

423
00:30:07,319 --> 00:30:08,079
I feel much more reassured.

424
00:30:08,319 --> 00:30:09,200
No need for formalities.

425
00:30:10,359 --> 00:30:11,599
I know exactly

426
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:12,359
what each of you

427
00:30:12,559 --> 00:30:13,799
is capable of.

428
00:30:14,359 --> 00:30:15,119
Stay focused.

429
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:16,039
Understood.

430
00:30:27,359 --> 00:30:27,839
Professor Qiao.

431
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:28,440
Here.

432
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:29,160
Prepare to de-air the aortic root.

433
00:30:29,599 --> 00:30:29,960
Okay.

434
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:36,799
Tianming.

435
00:30:37,119 --> 00:30:37,599
Inflate the lungs and de-air.

436
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:38,279
Copy.

437
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:15,640
Prepare to reduce flow.

438
00:31:16,359 --> 00:31:16,839
Reducing flow.

439
00:31:22,519 --> 00:31:23,440
Prepare to unclamp the aorta.

440
00:31:27,599 --> 00:31:28,279
Aortic clamp off.

441
00:31:29,319 --> 00:31:30,000
Restore flow.

442
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:15,880
Something's wrong.

443
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:17,079
Blood pressure is dropping.

444
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:18,559
Venous pressure is rising.

445
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:19,599
The right heart is distending.

446
00:32:28,759 --> 00:32:29,799
Acute right heart failure.

447
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:32,680
Once the right ventricle fails,

448
00:32:33,240 --> 00:32:34,279
blood can't be pumped into the lungs.

449
00:32:34,519 --> 00:32:35,720
The patient can become critical within minutes.

450
00:32:35,799 --> 00:32:37,160
It's one of the most dangerous

451
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:38,039
and deadliest complications

452
00:32:38,119 --> 00:32:39,720
in heart transplantation.

453
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:46,759
Director.

454
00:32:52,559 --> 00:32:53,039
Director.

455
00:32:55,319 --> 00:32:56,279
Professor Qiao, stop reducing flow.

456
00:32:56,799 --> 00:32:57,240
Copy.

457
00:33:00,279 --> 00:33:00,680
Tianming.

458
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:02,599
Give a pulmonary vasodilator.

459
00:33:02,759 --> 00:33:03,079
Okay.

460
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:11,240
Accurate and decisive.

461
00:33:11,799 --> 00:33:12,319
Now

462
00:33:12,799 --> 00:33:14,519
it depends on the patient's will to survive.

463
00:33:21,279 --> 00:33:22,000
Big Winter Melon,

464
00:33:25,519 --> 00:33:26,359
we're almost there.

465
00:33:27,680 --> 00:33:28,640
Hang on.

466
00:33:50,319 --> 00:33:51,079
Hold on.

467
00:34:02,119 --> 00:34:02,720
Blood pressure is coming back up.

468
00:34:05,880 --> 00:34:06,359
Xiaohu.

469
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:15,440
Cardiac contractility is good.

470
00:34:16,280 --> 00:34:17,840
Almost no mitral

471
00:34:17,880 --> 00:34:18,719
or tricuspid regurgitation.

472
00:34:19,719 --> 00:34:21,360
Volume loading looks good too.

473
00:34:25,920 --> 00:34:26,320
We did it.

474
00:34:58,559 --> 00:34:59,280
I have to say,

475
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:00,880
this guy's life

476
00:35:01,199 --> 00:35:02,400
is tougher than steel.

477
00:35:17,320 --> 00:35:17,880
Big Winter Melon,

478
00:35:20,039 --> 00:35:20,559
well done.

479
00:35:23,519 --> 00:35:24,320
May you live to a hundred.

480
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:37,519
Yi.

481
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:40,920
Yi.

482
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:44,320
Yi.

483
00:35:48,280 --> 00:35:49,119
You'll save me,

484
00:35:50,599 --> 00:35:51,039
right?

485
00:35:55,639 --> 00:35:56,519
I'll wait right here for you.

486
00:36:23,639 --> 00:36:24,159
Director.

487
00:36:27,960 --> 00:36:28,840
Why?

488
00:36:31,559 --> 00:36:32,119
Why?

489
00:36:32,119 --> 00:36:32,559
Xiaorui.

490
00:36:33,519 --> 00:36:34,519
Why?

491
00:36:37,119 --> 00:36:38,000
Why?

492
00:36:38,079 --> 00:36:38,800
What's wrong?

493
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:40,400
Why?

494
00:36:41,559 --> 00:36:44,199
Why couldn't he save me?

495
00:36:50,360 --> 00:36:51,519
Is it just because

496
00:36:51,519 --> 00:36:52,440
he wears a white coat?

497
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:57,159
Does he always have to be so noble?

498
00:37:00,079 --> 00:37:02,679
He's saved so many people.

499
00:37:04,440 --> 00:37:06,840
Why couldn't he save me for once?

500
00:37:13,719 --> 00:37:14,840
Sister Xiaoran.

501
00:37:15,480 --> 00:37:16,440
Why?

502
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:17,880
Xiaorui.

503
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:20,239
Don't be afraid.

504
00:37:22,559 --> 00:37:23,360
Let's get up first.

505
00:37:23,719 --> 00:37:25,760
I don't want Brother Dadong to die.

506
00:37:32,559 --> 00:37:34,079
But I want to live too.

507
00:37:36,599 --> 00:37:38,719
I want to live too!

508
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:42,559
Don't be afraid, Xiaorui.

509
00:37:44,639 --> 00:37:45,519
Let's get you up.

510
00:37:45,559 --> 00:37:47,000
You can't get this worked up.

511
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:47,599
Okay?

512
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:50,440
Come on.

513
00:37:50,840 --> 00:37:52,320
Be good. Get up.

514
00:37:52,400 --> 00:37:52,800
Come on.

515
00:38:10,760 --> 00:38:11,360
Xiaorui.

516
00:38:13,480 --> 00:38:14,159
Don't lose hope.

517
00:38:15,159 --> 00:38:16,239
There will be another chance.

518
00:39:17,840 --> 00:39:19,800
Xiaorui just can't accept it yet.

519
00:39:21,079 --> 00:39:22,239
He'll come around.

520
00:39:22,239 --> 00:39:23,400
He won't truly blame you.

521
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:26,079
He has every right to blame me.

522
00:39:29,719 --> 00:39:30,719
He should blame me.

523
00:39:37,239 --> 00:39:38,039
What comes next?

524
00:39:39,719 --> 00:39:40,519
What are you planning?

525
00:39:43,960 --> 00:39:45,000
I want to take him home.

526
00:39:54,039 --> 00:39:55,360
Should we try persuading him again

527
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:57,280
to get an LVAD?

528
00:39:58,159 --> 00:39:59,360
The new-generation fully magnetically levitated

529
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:00,159
left ventricular assist device

530
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:02,079
has a five-year survival rate

531
00:40:02,800 --> 00:40:04,400
almost equal to heart transplantation.

532
00:40:08,039 --> 00:40:09,079
He made it clear

533
00:40:11,159 --> 00:40:11,960
he doesn't want one.

534
00:40:13,639 --> 00:40:14,280
Then what about

535
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:15,119
a CRT-D?

536
00:40:17,199 --> 00:40:18,159
This time, his tests showed

537
00:40:19,239 --> 00:40:20,840
his ventricular synchrony

538
00:40:21,599 --> 00:40:22,320
isn't very good.

539
00:40:26,199 --> 00:40:27,159
I think it could help.

540
00:40:28,159 --> 00:40:28,880
The situation now

541
00:40:28,920 --> 00:40:30,079
is different from before.

542
00:40:31,119 --> 00:40:32,840
We can try talking to Xiaorui.

543
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:34,320
He knows

544
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:35,960
he's ranked fairly high now.

545
00:40:36,639 --> 00:40:37,159
That way,

546
00:40:37,159 --> 00:40:38,760
he can wait more safely for a donor.

547
00:40:41,599 --> 00:40:42,360
I'll ask him.

548
00:40:44,679 --> 00:40:45,639
It's his decision.

549
00:40:59,199 --> 00:40:59,599
Brother.

550
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:01,039
Go back to work.

551
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:02,920
Once he falls asleep,

552
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:03,719
I'll go in and stay with him.

553
00:41:21,360 --> 00:41:21,760
Let's go.
